The record is in the Church Book for Avnslev, Vindinge, Svensborg.  Familysearch's standardized place name is Skalkendrup, Aunslev, Vindinge, Svendborg, Denmark.  I am uncertain if "Aunslev" is a typo.  The record is a Baptism/Christening record on Palm Sunday in March of 1788 and they are using the "church holiday" system of dating.  In 1788 on the Danish calender, the full moon is 22 March so Easter Sunday is 23 March and Palm Sunday is on 16 March 1788.
